modules.description: Provides operations for constructing, manipulating, and evaluating reduced shared decision diagrams (RSDDs), including node creation, traversal, and canonical form conversion. Works with custom data types representing nodes, edges, and decision diagrams. Used to optimize and analyze logical expressions in symbolic computation tasks.

The module provides operations for constructing and manipulating binary decision diagrams (BDDs), including logical operations like AND, OR, ITE, and NOT, as well as weighted model counting and expected utility calculations. It works with BDD pointers, CNF formulas, and builder structures to enable logical inference and model counting. Specific use cases include compiling CNF formulas into BDDs and evaluating complex logical expressions with weight-based analysis.
